WATSON, Respondent, v. RUSSELL, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. May 17, 1894.) Action by Alice Watson against John H. Russell.

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

Vanderpoel, Cuming & Goodwin, for appellant. Van Duzer & Taylor, for respondent

No opinion. Motion for leave to appeal to the court of appeals granted. See 28 N. Y. Supp. 26.
